			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Overview:<br />
	This newly created position will build, implement and evaluate the appropriate social media strategies to support each product line. Work directly with cross functional teams to ensure go to market strategies are in line with social media strategies.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	Responsibilities:<br />
	Coordinate content and strategy across Sage North America from various internal and external sources<br />
	Develop a comprehensive social media strategy and implement appropriate new social media tools, from blogs to Facebook and wikis to LinkedIn and beyond<br />
	Analyze business objectives and develop appropriate social media strategies to support<br />
	Measure social media initiatives based on goals and success metrics<br />
	Develop and interpret sentiment reporting campaigns, evaluating findings to create strategic and tactical responses<br />
	Be an internal and external evangelist for social marketing to build an understanding of the practical benefits of this new medium, identify and implement best practices, and demonstrate passion, reason, and results<br />
	Collaborate cross functionally, to ensure community/social media initiatives coordinate with/complement other go-to-market strategies<br />
	Develop and manage outreach/engagement strategy for major industry trade groups<br />
	Other duties as assigned<br />
	Skills</p>
<p>
	Qualifications:<br />
	2+ experience as a subject matter expert on online social media tools<br />
	5+ years experience required in marketing management and/or B2B product/service marketing<br />
	Four-year degree (BA/BS) highly preferredDemonstrated accomplishments with new media strategy and execution: developing online communities, devising social media strategies, and interacting with partners/customers/employees/other stakeholders<br />
	Experience with web analytic tools and demonstrated ability to drive to measureable results<br />
	Experience in creating Web content and design<br />
	The qualified candidate will have demonstrated success in marketing strategy development; marketing program design; customer segmentation and competitive analysis; experience with and familiarity with an indirect sales channel model<br />
	The candidate must have excellent written and oral communication skills; the demonstrated ability to work cross-functionally; be a strategic and creative thinker; and strong analytical capacity<br />
	Strong project management skills<br />
	Personal qualities of passion and reason; a willingness to be hands-on and the ability to work independently; strong personal initiative and the desire to work in a fast-paced environment; persistence; and intellectual and interpersonal flexibility &nbsp;</p>
